<!-- Change Admin Password  -->
<div id="set_passcode">
	<h1>Admin Password</h1>
	<h2>Overview</h2>
	<p>
        	The Admin Password is used to sign in to this <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin website.
        	The <em>Admin Password</em> page allows you to change the Admin Password, and to set some security option relating to the Admin Password.
	</p>


	<h2>Change <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin Password</h2>
	<p>To change to current Admin Password, you must first enter the current Admin Password in the field below.
	The screen will then update, and provide the option to set a new Admin Password and a security question for use
	if the Admin Password is lost.
	</p>

	<h3>Current <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin Password</h3>
	<p>
        	Enter the current <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin Password in this field.
        	Note that if you enter an incorrect value too many times, you will be locked out of this <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin website.
        	To clear this lock, the <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> must be restarted.
	</p>
	<tmpl_if showDisplayPascode>
		<h2>Display the <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin Password</h2>
		<p>
			If this setting is ON, then ********* is displayed. If this setting is OFF, then the Admin Password can be read on the Jetpack's display.
		</p>
	</tmpl_if>

	<h2>Change <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name")> Admin Password</h2>
	<h3>New Admin Password</h3>
	<p>
	        Enter the new Admin Password, using only letters, numbers, and standard punctuation symbols.
        	The password must be at least 8 characters long.
	</p>

	<h3><tmpl_var truncate(_("webui", "set_passcode_confirm_passcode_label"), (size(_("webui", "set_passcode_confirm_passcode_label")) - size(":")))></h3>
	<p>
        	Re-enter the new Admin Password in this field.
	</p>

	<h3><tmpl_var truncate(_("webui", "set_passcode_security_question_label"), (size(_("webui", "set_passcode_security_question_label")) - size(":")))></h3>
	<p>This security question is used if the Admin Password is lost, and the "I forgot the Admin Password" option is used.
 	 Select the desired question, and provide an answer in the field below.
	</p>

	<h3><tmpl_var truncate(_("webui", "set_passcode_security_answer_label"), (size(_("webui", "set_passcode_security_answer_label")) - size(":")))></h3>
	<p>Provide an answer to the security question selected above.
	Note that answers are case-sensitive.
	</p>

</div>
<!-- id="set_passcode" -->

